Class FileManager<HeaderType extends PageHeader,PageType extends Page<HeaderType>,FileType extends StorageFile<HeaderType,PageType>>

@HW1.CS316Todo

public class FileManager<HeaderType extends PageHeader,PageType extends Page<HeaderType>,FileType extends StorageFile<HeaderType,PageType>>
extends java.lang.Object

Manages a collection of files belonging to the database. A FileManager provides an interface to the files which hold the data in the database. Files can be added directly, or as part of a relation. Files in turn contain pages, the reading and writing of which are managed by a buffer pool. Note this class is not thread-safe. Callers must implement table-level locking to ensure consistency with multi-threaded relation manipulation.

readPage

@HW1.CS316Todo
@HW1.CS416Todo
public PageType readPage(PageType buf,
                                                     PageId id)
Reads the on-disk page corresponding to the given page id into the given buffer. The page id must be a valid on-disk page, that is, its file id must correspond to a database file tracked by this file manager.

Parameters:
buf - an in-memory page supplied by the buffer pool which is filled by the page from disk
id - the identifier of the page being accessed
Returns:
the buffer if the page is successfully read, otherwise null

writePage

@HW1.CS416Todo
public int writePage(PageType page)
Writes the given page to the on-disk location specified by the page's identifier. This page id must contain a valid file id corresponding to a database file tracked by this file manager.

Parameters:
page - a page to be written to disk
Returns:
the number of bytes written by this operation

getWriteablePage

@HW1.CS316Todo
@HW1.CS416Todo
public PageId getWriteablePage(TableId rel,
                                                           short requestedSpace,
                                                           java.util.Collection<PageId> cached)
Searches the database files for the given relation, looking for a page with the requested free space. This method also accepts a list of pages cached by the buffer pool to exclude from consideration since they should already have been inspected at this point.

Parameters:
rel - the relation to which we want to write
requestedSpace - the amount of space requested
cached - a collection of page ids for cached pages that have been checked
Returns:
the page id of a suitable page in the files for the relation
